verses.text:
Then pleased it the apostles and elders, with the whole church, to send chosen men of their own company to Antioch with Paul and Barnabas;
namely,
 Judas surnamed Barsabas, and Silas, chief men among the brethren:

And when the governor had read
the letter, he asked of what province he was. And when he understood that
he was of Cilicia;

And because the haven was not commodious to winter in, the more part advised to depart thence also, if by any means they might attain to Phenice,
and there to winter;
which is an haven of Crete, and lieth toward the south west and north west.

And we being exceedingly tossed with a tempest, the next
day
 they lightened the ship;
